# Production-Grade Django Authentication System

A step-by-step guide to build a full authentication system with Django + MySQL.  
**You type everything manually** — each block of code is explained so you understand *why* it exists.

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Client] --> B[Django REST Framework]
    B --> C[Custom User Model]
    C --> D[MySQL Database]
    B --> E[JWT Token Auth]
    B --> F[Email Verification]
    B --> G[Password Reset]
    B --> H[Rate Limiting]
    E --> I[Access Token - 15min]
    E --> J[Refresh Token - 7days]
    F --> K[Token-based Email Confirm]
    G --> L[Secure Reset Flow]
```

### What We're Building

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| Custom User Model | Email-based login instead of username |
| JWT Authentication | Access + Refresh tokens (not session-based) |
| Email Verification | Users must verify email before full access |
| Password Reset | Secure token-based password reset via email |
| Rate Limiting | Prevent brute-force attacks |
| Security Headers | CSRF, CORS, XSS protection |
| Input Validation | Proper serializer-level validation |

