**Why these settings matter:**

- `DEFAULT_AUTHENTICATION_CLASSES` — Every API view uses JWT by default. No more session cookies.
- `DEFAULT_PERMISSION_CLASSES` — Every endpoint requires authentication by default. You explicitly mark public endpoints with `AllowAny`. This is the "secure by default" principle — it's safer to forget to add `IsAuthenticated` to one view than to forget to add `AllowAny`.
- `DEFAULT_THROTTLE_RATES` — Anonymous users: 20 requests/minute. Authenticated users: 60/minute. This prevents brute-force login attacks and API abuse.

