**Why these specific values?**

| Setting | Value | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `ACCESS_TOKEN_LIFETIME` | 15 minutes | Short-lived. If stolen, the attacker has a small window. |
| `REFRESH_TOKEN_LIFETIME` | 7 days | User stays logged in for a week without re-entering credentials. |
| `ROTATE_REFRESH_TOKENS` | True | Every time you use a refresh token, you get a *new* one. The old one is invalidated. |
| `BLACKLIST_AFTER_ROTATION` | True | The old refresh token is added to a blacklist so it can't be reused. Prevents replay attacks. |
| `UPDATE_LAST_LOGIN` | True | Updates the `last_login` field on the User model whenever a token is issued. Useful for admin dashboards. |

